Text.Value: I remember the first time you set foot in the Tribunal. Fallen paladin, coated in the blood of your order. Pure corruption, I knew you would go far.

RuleGroup.RuleString: BARD or SORCERER or WARLOCK or WIZARD

Text.Value: You will die here, mageling. Paltry spells will not save you now.
You will make a most beautiful offering to the Lord of Murder.
Minsc knows little of irony, but he would be happy to show you his steel again, Sarevok.

EditorData.NodeContext: Saying 'irony' like 'iron' - distaste and anger at seeing Sarevok again

Text.Value: And you will be well-instructed. For you follow a Bhaalspawn.
Blood will be spilt, Sarevok. I will slaughter you.
Civilian, do not listen to this ancient fuck. Free me at once.
Go, berserker. Do as you do best - but this time in the name of Murder.

EditorData.logicalname: MINSC ACTIVE PLAYER UNHOLY ASS HASMET

Text.Value: But you have brought it crashing at our Father's feet. With Orin's death and your rejection of him, you leave him with no Chosen.
You failed to protect her.
The family tree is a bit of a circle, isn't it?
Aren't you sad I killed your granddaughter?
Even by Bhaal's standards, you're truly vile, uncle.
The reasons matter not. The celestial is dead. The offering is made.

EditorData.NodeContext: authoritative, addressing the room at large

Text.Value: The Grand Harper - baptised in blood. What a sight to behold.
To receive the Blessing of Bhaal... I lie awake each night, in this sleepless scab of a form... dreaming of what it would have been like.
A word of advice, Unholy Assassin - wrap your leash tighter about your slaves, lest their belligerence undoes you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to player, with fatherly tone, as one Bhaalist to another

Text.Value: In my Father's name, I will sacrifice this creature.
I will sacrifice the creature to Bhaal.
I will rise again, the Dread Lord's Chosen once again. And you will be my offering.
And so I am exposed to the instincts of a pure Bhaalspawn. I should have known. Yours is a nature not to be contained.
There is nothing more I can teach you, but if you bring about her death, return to me. We shall revel in the divine memory together, as Family.
Stumble on, Rasheman wanderer... murder well in His name.

EditorData.logicalname: HASMET MINSC ACTIVE PLAYER UNHOLY ASSASSIN

Text.Value: Sarevok, Bhaal's least favourite son. Still tied to daddy's apron-strings?

EditorData.NodeContext: Jeering - she's meeting an old enemy from the previous games

Text.Value: Slaughter deeply, aspirant, then bathe in the font of blood. The Murder Lord awaits your offering.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Valeria present, but not yet killed by player in gameplay

Text.Value: Bhaal below, I really just want to kill you.
They know I am more than my lineage. You do not.
There is much left to do. This world must surrender to him.
While Bhaal receives tribute through Orin, He lives again through you.
Our friend is not like you were, Sarevok. When Boo speaks to her of goodness, she does not get that stupid, soon-to-sneeze look on her face, as you used to.
Our friend is not like you were, Sarevok. When Boo speaks to him of goodness, he does not get that stupid, soon-to-sneeze look on his face, as you used to.
Our friend is not like you were, Sarevok. When Boo speaks to them of goodness, they does not get that stupid, soon-to-sneeze look on their face, as you used to.
And in the end she died for nothing. By your hand. The whole debacle caused naught but Bhaal's ire.
Remember. We are here to find our way into Bhaal's Temple. Not to enter his service in truth.

EditorData.NodeContext: Pitched low to player alone - we are playing the role of Bhaal's faithful as an act, we can't get lost in it

Text.Value: Take this amulet, child, and return it to your Father's chamber.
Walk in blood, Unholy Assassin. It is Lord Bhaal's will.
I discovered she was the sire of your own incest. Now your line is ended.
I told Orin your secret, Sarevok. That she was both your granddaughter and your daughter. She couldn't bear it.

EditorData.logicalname: TOLD ORIN SHE IS SAREVOK'S DAUGHTER

Text.Value: No more, Sarevok. It's time someone put an end to you.
You're disgusting, siring a child from your own daughter.
With this amulet, He grants you entry to His chambers - the undercity Temple of Bhaal.
You have given me everything a father could hope for.
Why did you order Orin's mother to kill her?
Feisty little creature. If you hold it down, I will slice off its trunk.
It will make a fine pair of ivory daggers.
I didn't deserve an eternity of rest, I deserved only this shackle, to live forever on the outskirts of my own dear cult, and mourn my own downfall.
I knew the old way. Two feral Bhaalpups, jostling for position at the top. One was going to die by the other's hand.
Perhaps your heart has spent too long bleeding. Bhaal will not allow for a moment of weakness.
Do not keep your Father waiting. Slaughter first, then cleanse yourself in blood.
Join me. We shred her together.
I sowed the seeds of my intent. It was you that harvested them.
Why do you wait, child of Murder? Bathe now in the font of blood and receive your Father's blessing.

EditorData.logicalname: HASMET DU + VALERIA NOT PRESENT + NOT BAPTISED

Text.Value: What better offering to make to our Lord?
Killing is but another vital function of your existence. Such is the Urge.
And now that you have returned, we will have a new age of slaughter in your name. For you have slain Orin in our Father's Temple.
But do not let us keep you from your business. There is so very much sitting and sulking in the darkness to be done.
You wear our Lord's will well. Go forth and render murder in his name.
For you, His perfect creation, it is only natural.
Boo will leave your innards unfeasted on for now, Sarevok, but only to leave room for the villains who actually matter.

EditorData.NodeContext: Scorn and distaste. As harsh a burn as Minsc can levy

Text.Value: I will be the last of my line.
Make violence of its goodness. Spill its blood, and bathe in Bhaal's eternal rapture.
And every day living with the failure of my first death, I wondered... whether Bhaal might forgive me.
Come, child of Bhaal. Offer thanks unto your father for your birth, and in so doing, be reborn anew.
No more than you are, Harper. For you have been reborn. And in our service are we united, Unholy Assassin.
You stand now on the cusp of the Dread Lord's favour.
Slaughter this celestial being. Spill its blood into the void and through eradication of its goodness, be exalted.
Bow before me, Sarevok. I have accomplished more than you ever dreamed of.
Bhaal never had a more fecund offering than I sowed on his behalf.
It felt wonderful...
With your death, will I prove myself anew. It is Father's way.
BETRAYER.
The child of Bhaal who slays the Chosen may himself become Bhaal's Chosen.
We act with a purpose, Sarevok. Perhaps you have forgotten what that feels like.
What a treat. Just like your granddaughter was, gargling on her own blood.
I bestow upon you the Amulet of Bhaal - the vestment of his most unholy servants.
You failed to bring forth issue while you helmed our cult. It is a mortal sin for a Chosen.
They are powerful allies - I need all the help I can get.
And every death a prayer.
That's pure delusion. Bhaal would never anoint you as the Chosen, worm.
A true pleasure this will be, Bhaalspawn. Whether to kill you or to be killed by you.
You don't recall all the wrong you wrought at the Temple, champion of the underworld. But one matter is undeniable:
Now you may experience my talents firsthand. I am here to kill you.
You slaughtered well. Your worth is proven. Enter now the font of blood and be reborn.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Valeria not present at all - player killed her already prior to Murder Tribunal.

Text.Value: Why would you make a child with your own child?
Poor child, she doted on her grandfather, the only person who tried to protect her when her mother failed to kill her.
I am pleased she died a finer offering yet: there is no deeper honour than death in a duel with Bhaal's Chosen.
You are truly disgusting, Sarevok.
The temple is beneath the city, where all blood spilled is drained.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: We see a shot of the player emerging from the blood, it cascades down from their face. We see them open their eyes: pitch black. They blink once, and their eyes are normal again.

Text.Value: Do not presume any would follow your path, Sarevok. After all, you've shown them its sad and meaningless end.

EditorData.NodeContext: Scorn for Sarevok, pushing back on the notion that he's won by influence the player. Gesturing at the sad and dark surrounds on last line.

Text.Value: I'm surprised you would have me as Chosen, over your own granddaughter.
The thwarted dream of two centuries ago - for Father to walk the planes again - you are the one that can revive that dream.
And yet I returned to my Father's service, and brought you with me, Rasheman wanderer. For in your baptism are we united under Bhaal.
The discards of history may yet find their true purpose in Bhaal's service.
Take pleasure in your slaughters, Harper, and relish your unholy acts of murder.

EditorData.logicalname: HASMET JAHEIRA ACTIVE PLAYER UNHOLY ASS

Text.Value: After centuries of this rancid defeat, I rejoice. For today, I meet the true definition of failure.
As my daughter raised our daughter, we debated to no end as to how we would make of her the perfect offering to the Dread Lord.
It is a shame you did not tell her. Orin never knew who her father was. Never knew how potent he could be.
I played your game, but I will go no further.
Thus, one would halve the work, of murdering to the top. They would never consider that another remained yet with a claim upon their title. You didn't even think of it when we spoke earlier.
Father shall be proud, indeed. Go to him, and present your sister as an offering. There isn't a moment to lose.
Behold Father Bhaal! Your lost child, bathed anew. Arise, Unholy Assassin!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: We see the player walk into the pool of blood, submerging themselves

Text.Value: You have slain my granddaughter, Orin.
Behold, Father. Baptised in your most wretched name: a new Unholy Assassin.

EditorData.AnimationTags: We see the player walk into the pool of blood, submerging themselves
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: We see the player walk into the pool of blood, submerging themselves

Text.Value: Ah, faces I have not beheld for a long time. Nature's warrior and the idiot ranger.
She gave up before she died, when she heard of her mother's hate.
One who dies for no other reason than the sanctity of slaughter.
You have been found wanting.
You are so full of promise, the perfect Chosen. I almost hate to bring a challenge upon you.
The victorious Chosen must emerge from his own knife-arm. Far be it from me to bend Bhaal's will.
This is grim. If we can slip this without murdering a hollyphant, I'll be very glad.
And who counselled you to do it?
Perhaps not, but for his honour, I must try. To die by the hand of a Chosen is the only death I could ever wish to take.
Do not test the Murder Lord's patience. Bathe now in the font of blood, and be baptised as His Unholy Assassin.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Hasmet for the case where player had already killed Valeria prior to entering the Murder Tribunal (so didn't make the sacrifice in this scene.)
EditorData.logicalname: HASMET VALERIA NOT PRESENT + NOT BATHED IN BLOOD

Text.Value: Today we witness near-perfection, Bhaalspawn. Your blood was foul before, but now you are twice-tarnished - the Unholiest Assassin.
Come, child of Bhaal. You have wrought exquisite murder. Enter now the font of blood and be purified in sin.
I will be the last of our line. As long as one Bhaalspawn lives yet, there may be a Chosen.
Your despicable sister lies dead, and your Chosen body bathed in her blood.
One killing secures your rebirth as an Unholy Assassin of Bhaal - the slaughter of a celestial being.
Your talents have outstripped my expectations.

EditorData.NodeContext: impressed when any normal person would be disgusted/upset

Text.Value: I wish he trusted me to act on my own, without forcing my hand.
And yet you still live, Sarevok, after all these years.
You return, Unholy Assassin, soaked with the stench of one familiar to me...

EditorData.logicalname: UNHOLY ASSASSIN + NOT DU + ORIN DEAD

Text.Value: As followers of a Bhaalspawn.
You have done me a great service, Child of Murder. In eliminating Orin, you have cleared the way for me.
Cleanse the temple of Orin's girlish shrines and bring your primal slaughter back to Bhaal.
Take this amulet, child, and return it to your Father's chamber. You are the true inheritor of his will, and he would smile to see you wear it.
Come on, I did the work of killing her. I'm the one worth his respect.
I should raise a hymnal in your name, child. For the service you have done for me.

EditorData.NodeContext: pause before he says this with a sickly smile

Text.Value: UNWORTHY.
Bhaal's line should have ended with you, Sarevok - how is it that you still live?
Minsc does the doing, Boo the reasoning why - and he need not explain our noble cause to you, smooth-skull.
You have been judged.
You ordered her own mother to kill her. I simply finished the job.

EditorData.logicalname: TOLD ORIN SAREVOK ORDERED MUM TO KILL HER

Text.Value: Bhaal's will is absolute. The strongest of his bloodline will be Chosen. A spawn who kills a Chosen must then become Chosen themselves.
Go now, and do what I could not. Go to the heart of slaughter, and be the last to live.
And I remember my battle for the city like it was yesterday...
Two hundred years late, but your hold over the Gate ends today.
I failed once to kill my kin. Now, at last may I offer family blood to the Lord.
I did. And now I'm here to bathe this place in yours.
It must have been. And you have given me new hope yet.
Who laid a trap for the hot-blooded young Bhaalspawn, and tricked them to return?
And, would you know it, little Slayer, so do I you.
Kill this celestial being, make violence of its goodness, and you will be reborn - an Unholy Assassin of Bhaal.
Tell me, Unholy Assassin. Why waste your time on discarded relics? With Bhaal's favour you need them not.
Chk. Would you be so cowardly as to do the bidding of this turgid dread-lord?
Worship death though I do, I refused it. I roamed the Coast, gathering those who still held Bhaal in their black hearts.
It was beyond any dreams.
I shall be his very body on this world.
Chk. Any sacrifice we make must be for my venerable queen, not this turgid dread-lord.
Father loves no sport more than the spillages of fratricide.
A long while ago, my wretched sibling brought me back. The fairest of Bhaalspawn, soul-bound me to this husk.
I'd hoped she would die by the Chosen's hand. But there is no Chosen in this cruel world, and soon I shall be all that remains of his line.
Tribute is not enough for our Lord. She dies.
I died, once. A death in the selfsame temple chamber where you slaughtered Orin.
Our cult survived, festering beneath the city, with me as the Gate's everlasting poison.
The cult survived, festering beneath the city, with me as the Gate's everlasting poison.
Outrageous. If Bhaal demands blood, you cannot, you must not, be the one to spill it for him.
You don't have a hope in the Hells of defeating me.
To eat her when she was but a babe? To drain a gallon of her blood each morn and pour it over his icon each night? To skin her, and craft the hide into a hilt for a sacred knife?
Go now child. Slaughter your sister, Orin. Take your rightful place as Father's heir.
Another walks in Bhaal's bloody footsteps. It seems your warnings were not heeded, 'heroes' of Baldur's Gate.
I told Orin the truth about you - that you ordered her own mother to kill her.
The portfolio of murder passes into your hands. Do it justice. Enact slaughter befitting a god.

EditorData.AnimationTags: The player emerges from the pool of blood

EditorData.logicalname: Alias (IF MADE OUT J/M ARE OUR SLAVES)

Text.Value: Courting Bhaal's favour is but a means to an end. I am no acolyte of murder.
Do not mistake my blessing. If it is your death that becomes the offering, I would worship that tragedy.
The noble Jaheira - once more walking in Bhaal's bloody footsteps.
My aching bones in this husk still feel every spark of pain from the crystalline moment of my first death, in the Temple.
With these killings, the glory of the Bhaalists has risen beyond what we dreamed possible during those dark days.
I fell from my position at Bhaal's helm - why am I still worthy to become Chosen?
Oi, I know you! Do not listen to this ancient fuck. Free me at once.
I even hoped you and my daughter might one day create a new blood-lamb for us, but it is not to be...
Genuflect before my divine body, for I am Bhaal's new Chosen.
I fear very greatly when he possesses me.
Bhaal's seed must be sown throughout the land that He might wreak murder on the world entire.
And yet, as you came afore Bhaal, you spat upon the glory all of our brood dream of so deeply.
Every Bhaalspawn, other than he who would be Chosen, is born to die.
Does your body force you to blink? To breathe? To piss?
Leaving Father with no Chosen at all.
Very well. But first, I will slaughter you.
You always were vulnerable to a grand narrative. Such weakness is common among heroes of your ilk.
Perhaps Father will take me back if I clean the world of his little embarrassment.
This is Bhaal's sacrifice...? Wouldn't have been my first guess. Or my tenth.

EditorData.NodeContext: Surprised. The sacrifice is a hollyphant, a small, cute talking elephant with wings

Text.Value: I must admit it brings me pleasure to baptise an Unholy Assassin in your presence, noble heroes.
By spilling Orin's blood, you rouse an old man's withered passions from their slumber, and clear the way for their awakening.
Child of Bhaal: do you not fear our Father's wrath? Why waste your time on discarded relics? With Bhaal's blood in your veins, you need them not.
You have slaughtered Bhaal's Chosen, yes. But I will not bow to you.
Yes, Boo - Sarevok does speak like one who has not tasted Minsc's boot on his brow before. You will recall we killed you once before, Bhaalspawn.
I loved her as I loved her mother. One born from the other, both heritors of my essence.
To strangle it with its own trunk! Yes... Yes!
It shall play a symphony of screams with its trumpet!
You belong to Bhaal. He manifests within you. And you are a truer vessel of his cruelty than even the Slayer could be.
She doted on her grandfather, the only person who tried to protect her when her mother failed to kill her.
She withered when I told her your truth - that she was to be her mother's sacrifice.
The hamstered fool - once more stumbling across Bhaal's bloody path.
I'm no Bhaalspawn. Not any longer.
You have proven capable of killing those known to you, but true devotion is the killing of an innocent. One who never had reason to wrong you.
For two hundred years, I wallowed in my own failure to dominate this city.
I never credited Bhaal with a sense of humour. This is some sick joke of his - let's not be part of it.
This is the grand sacrifice demanded by Bhaal? This?
This leathered balloon is bound. Helpless. If there must be blood spilled on this floor, Boo has some better ideas of who it should belong to.

EditorData.NodeContext: Pitched low, urgent - Minsc doesn't want to sacrifice the hollyphant, he wants to kill Sarevok instead

Text.Value: Let us die, Chosen, as only Bhaalspawn can.
This is the sacrifice that Bhaal demands? I had expected something more... auspicious, perhaps.

EditorData.NodeContext: Surprised. The sacrifice is a hollyphant, a small, cute talking elephant with wings

Text.Value: Spare no violence for the Dread Lord's grace. And savour every moment of the creature's slaughter.
Yet you still came here - seeking Lord Bhaal's favour.
To arms, then. In Bhaal's name.
You will never know. You failed.
That's none of your business.
No, I am proud.
Your wits remain as sharp as ever. But your devotion must be sharper still - for you now carry the Murder Lord's blessing, Unholy Assassin, and his expectation.
You return, taint-blessed kin-killer, having committed the holiest of sins.
I know the truth, Sarevok. Orin wasn't just your granddaughter. She was your daughter, too.

EditorData.logicalname: KNOWS SAREVOK-ORIN RELATIONSHIP + DIDNT TELL ORIN

Text.Value: Sarevok, Bhaal's least favourite son. Still tied to daddy's apron-strings?

EditorData.NodeContext: Jeering - she's meeting an old enemy from the previous games

Text.Value: HIS MOST UNHOLY WILL BE DONE.
It matters not. The celestial is dead. The offering is made.

EditorData.NodeContext: authoritative, addressing the room at large

Text.Value: Pah. All this birth is a distraction. The world over will be dead soon enough.

Synopsis: The trial of the Murder Tribunal culminates in the Baptism of Blood, in the abattoir. The Tribunal will have either abducted Valeria, the Hollyphant detective, and chained her up here in order to be sacrificed, or she is already dead and you will just need to bathe in her blood.
